 fixed frame but a movable track in the background. Used for values that have a discrete nature to them but would not necessarily fit on screen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Both the thumb and track can be dragged, if the track is dragged and thrown the velocity of the throw is added to the tracks velocity and it slows gradually to a stop."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the thumb is currently being dragged and reachs the minimum or maximum value of its bounds, velocity is added to the track in the opposite direction of the drag."}]},"doc://Sliders/tutorials/LSlider-Tutorials":{"kind":"overview","type":"topic","title":"Building Sliders with LSlider","role":"overview","url":"\/tutorials\/lslider-tutorials","identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/tutorials\/LSlider-Tutorials","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to add a spatially adaptive linear slider to your app — starting with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"built-in default style and its full range of configuration options, then advancing to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building a completely custom style from scratch."}]},"doc://Sliders/documentation/Sliders/DoubleLSlider":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DoubleLSlider","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/DoubleLSlider","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/sliders\/doublelslider","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DoubleLSlider"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A spatially adaptive linear range slider with a lower thumb, an upper thumb,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and a draggable active-track segment between them."}],"title":"DoubleLSlider"},"doc://Sliders/documentation/Sliders/LSliderStyle":{"title":"LSliderStyle","abstract":[{"text":"A style that determines the appearance of an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":